<PolicyPage ID="x26397" Name="Evaluation Criteria" Layout="general_Policy.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Policy Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Evaluation Criteria</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Policy Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Evaluation Criteria</Abstract><Date type="date" label="Revision Date" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true" display="localdateshort" UTC="true">20130909T18:00:00</Date><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Policy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;">The following criteria will be used in determining if travel involving students should be authorized:</p>
<ol style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;">
<li><strong>Purpose or Benefit</strong> - The experience should enhance the overall educational experience of students and/or advance the institution.</li>
<li><strong>Individual Well-Being</strong> - Travel should be executed in such a way where risks, liability, student time away from classes, and impact on adult supervisors are manageable and acceptable.</li>
<li><strong>Cost</strong> - The cost of the experience should be kept to a minimum, thereby making it as affordable to students as possible. Student travel should not impose an unbudgeted financial burden on departments or the institution as a whole.</li>
<li><strong>Accountability</strong> - Those sponsoring student travel are responsible for ensuring that institutional travel policies and procedures are followed.</li>
</ol>
